                    <h2>IRD AND ViPR</h2>
                    <img class="ird-vipr-logo" src="/patric/images/bv-brc/ird-vipr-logo.png" alt="IRD and ViPR Logo">
                    <p>The Influenza Research Database (IRD) and Virus Pathogen Database (ViPR) are the legacy Viral Bioinformatics Resource Centers, providing resources for the virus research communities that facilitate understanding of viral pathogens and how they interact with the host organism, leading to new treatments and preventive actions. These resources contain non-human surveillance data, human clinical data associated with virus extracts, phenotypic characteristics of viruses isolated from extracts, and all publicly available viral genomic and proteomic data. IRD/ViPR provide a suite of tools for analysis of all types of viral data and a personal work bench on which scientists can store lists of important data from the resources.</p>
